n she was moved June 7 to <LOCATION> Gaylord </LOCATION>. By midsummer, she was reading novels, relearning basic math skills and calling colleagues at <LOCATION> Salomon </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Bros. </LOCATION>, where she had worked before the attack. Main said the jogger and her family thanked the public and press for their support over the past seven months, saying it `` made a difference in her ability to recover.'' The family also thanked the news media for respecting her privacy and anonymity and stressed that the woman's continued recovery `` is highly dependent'' on these being maintained, Main said.
