wer to regulate the content of taped messages or live conversations. `` No one is prohibiting them from speaking. If people want to spend 50 minutes on the phone with <PERSON> Stella </PERSON> or 30 minutes with <PERSON> Raquel </PERSON>, they have the right and the companies have the right to provide that service,'' said <PERSON> Walsh </PERSON>. `` But we're not going to do the billing and collecting. With this kind of thing, it's easy to see people getting carried away and then not wanting to pay the bill when it comes due.''
