at will go to <LOCATION> Poland </LOCATION> Nov. 28 - Dec. 2 to help <LOCATION> Poland </LOCATION> restructure its economy <ORGANIZATION> Congress </ORGANIZATION> is nearing final approval of a package of about $ 800 million in economic aid for <LOCATION> Poland </LOCATION> and <LOCATION> Hungary </LOCATION>, steps that have the backing of the administration. In accusing <PERSON> Bush </PERSON> of trying to weaken <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION> unions, <PERSON> Mitchell </PERSON> in particular cited <PERSON> Bush </PERSON>'s refusal to intervene and block the 8-months-old <ORGANIZATION> Eastern </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Airlines </ORGANIZATION> strike. <PERSON> Bush </PERSON> has refused to use his power to name an emergency mediation board. `` They're all for labor unions as long as they are in <LOCATION> Poland </LOCATION> or some other country, anywhere but the <LOCATION> United </LOCATION> <LOCATION> States </LOCATION>,'' <PERSON> Mitchell </PERSON> said. Labor is awaiting word on whether <PERSON> Bush </PERSON> will sign a measure calling for a congressional study of the Eastern strike designed to produce recommendations for a settlement. `` If he ca n't do that -LRB- sign the bill -RRB- I do n't think labor can expect too much from him,'' said <PERSON> Susan </PERSON> <PERSON> Bianchi-Sand </PERSON>, president of the <ORGANIZATION> Association </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> of </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Flight </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Attendants </ORGANIZATION> and newly elected member of the federation's governing Executive Council. `` I do n't hold out hope that will sign it.'' <PERSON> Kirkland </PERSON>, meanwhile, was unanimously re-elected to a sixth-two year term. <PERSON> Thomas </PERSON> <PERSON> Donahue </PERSON> was the unanimous choice to continue as the federation's secretary
