oration,'' he said. `` I play a man who is beginning to believe in Marshal <PERSON> Petain </PERSON> and think the Germans are n't so bad. Then he has a change of heart and becomes a follower of <PERSON> Charles </PERSON> <PERSON> de </PERSON> <PERSON> Gaulle </PERSON>. `` When I met with the director he told me it would be the story of a man who enlists in the Free French Forces. I said, ` Oh, that's easy That's what I did in real life.' There was a long silence and he said, ` Yes, but you play the father.' I had simply forgotten about my age.'' Another completed film due for release soon is `` Les Grandes Familles.'' In recent years, <PERSON> Aumont </PERSON> has appeared on French television regularly and on <LOCATION> American </LOCATION> TV in such shows as `` <PERSON> Hart </PERSON> to <PERSON> Hart </PERSON>'' and `` The Love Boat.'' `` I did ` <PERSON> Gigi </PERSON>' on the stage in <LOCATION> London </LOCATION> for a year,'' he said. `` That was great fun. I had seven songs and I'm not really a singer. I told my agent, ` I'm not a singer.' He said, ` What about <PERSON> Rex </PERSON> <PERSON> Harrison </PERSON>? What about <PERSON> Maurice </PERSON> <PERSON> Chevalier </PERSON>?' I let myself be easily convinced.''
