<HEAD>Struggling Eastern Airlines Keeps Winter Fares Low</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By DAN SEWELL</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>MIAMI (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 Money-losing <ORGANIZATION> Eastern </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Airlines </ORGANIZATION> is keeping cut-rate fares to <LOCATION> Florida </LOCATION> this winter in an effort to bring back passengers, officials said Wednesday. `` What we're really doing is generating revenue,'' said <PERSON> George </PERSON> <PERSON> Brennan </PERSON>, <ORGANIZATION> Eastern </ORGANIZATION>'s vice president for marketing. `` We know a lot about <LOCATION> Florida </LOCATION> and how to stimulate travel ... We have an awful lot of seats coming into <LOCATION> Florida </LOCATION> this winter. `` The existing fare structure ... is a fare structure that is doing nothing to stimulate travel into <LOCATION> Florida </LOCATION>,'' <PERSON> Brennan </PERSON> said. `` Our objective obviously is to make money.'' The fares, with relatively few restrictions, are effective immediately for travel between nine <LOCATION> Florida </LOCATION> cities and 45 other <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION> cities. They are significant because the airline industry usually boosts winter season fares to vacation points, Eastern officials said. The majority of fliers to <LOCATION> Florida </LOCATION> are discretionary, or leisure travelers, <PERSON> Brennan </PERSON> said, spurring Eastern to offer incentives to them. A <LOCATION> Miami-to-New </LOCATION> <LOCATION> York </LOCATION> fare, based on round-trip purchase, would be $ 99 each way midweek, compared with a current fare of $ 139. In many cases, Eastern is maintaining `` back-in-business'' discount fares aimed at regaining business lost since the airline was hit by a strike on March 4 and entered Chapter 11 bankruptcy reorganization five days later. Passengers must make reservations before Dec. 15 and purchase their tickets _ if space is available _ seven days in advance. The tickets are fully refundable, <PERSON> Brennan </PERSON> said. Although the fares are part of a winter promotion, reservations can be made for anytime in the future, he said, and will be honored with seven-day advance purchase. The fares require two-night stays, but the nights do n't have to be on a weekend, he said. Blackout dates, on which normal fares apply, are southbound -LRB- into <LOCATION> Florida </LOCATION> -RRB- Dec. 21-26 and northbound -LRB- out of <LOCATION> Florida </LOCATION> -RRB- Jan. 1-3. A fare structure effective Jan. 6 will continue to offer discounts below industry averages but about $ 20 each way higher than <ORGANIZATION> Eastern </ORGANIZATION>'s bargain fares. Miami-based Eastern is flying 335 flights in and out of the nine <LOCATION> Florida </LOCATION> cities: <LOCATION> Miami </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Fort </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Lauderdale </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> West </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Palm </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Beach </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Tampa </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Orlando </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Daytona </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Beach </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Sarasota </LOCATION>, <PERSON> Fort </PERSON> <PERSON> Myers </PERSON> and <LOCATION> Melbourne </LOCATION>. Eastern's announcement came after last week's third-quarter report showed a net loss of $ 185.2 million amid indications the airline has informed its major creditors of a $ 200 million cash shortfall. `` It is used more as a marketing tool to attract attention,'' said <PERSON> Robert </PERSON> <PERSON> Joedicke </PERSON>, an airline analyst with <ORGANIZATION> Shearson </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Lehman </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Hutton </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Inc. </ORGANIZATION> in <LOCATION> New </LOCATION> <LOCATION> York </LOCATION>. `` It's calculated to create a loss, but it's calculated to regain critical mass, or market share. -LRB- Eastern must -RRB- be particularly active to win people back.'' Eastern officials, trying to rebuild without the unions, have said the airline will emerge from bankruptcy early next year at nearly 90 percent its pre-strike size. Eastern is back to 775 daily flights, compared with nearly 1,100 before the ongoing strike began.
